<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-11-22T10:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-11-22T10:00:00-05:00" n="635" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d635">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">811.248/791: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé at Tangier</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Childs</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Tangier</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-11-22T16:00:00+01:00">November
                                    22, 1942—4 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 6:07 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>681. The Chief of the Diplomatic Cabinet of the High Commissariat at
                            Tetuán telephoned on behalf of General Orgaz to state that the three
                            American planes which made forced landings in Spanish Morocco on
                            November 8 have been sent this morning to Madrid in accordance with
                            instructions of the Spanish Government.</p>
                        <pb facs="0534" n="522" xml:id="pg_522"/>
                        <p>I asked how they were sent and the statement was made that no details
                            were available.</p>
                        <p>Repeated to Madrid.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Childs</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>